ABAKALIKI – Ahead of Ebonyi State Local Government Elections bill for July 30th, 2022, the Chairmanship Aspirant for Afikpo South Council position on the platform of the All Progressives Congress (APC) Mr Chima Ekumankama, has pledged to unite the people and enhance development in the area. Ekumankama stated this shortly after submitting his expression of interest and nomination forms at the party’s secretariat, on Tuesday, in Abakaliki, the state capital. Ekumankama who was companied by a large crowd of supporters and stakeholders of the area, said the Council was badly challenged by disunity, and vowed to change the narratives if elected. He said: “We have been challenged with disunity in our place and that needs to be tackled, and from the support I’m getting so far, and the cooperation of my people, we will restore back peace, unity, oneness in Edda land. “And in terms of development, we will work with both political actors and none actors, to attract a lot for the good people of Edda land”, Chima pledged. Ekumankama said he would create an atmosphere that would enable home interface and interact with the youths and keep in touch with them, so as to make them understand the need to work hard to achieve success, rather than indulging in social vices such as cultism, among others. He commended Governor David Umahi for the infrastructural development in Afikpo South and pledged to work for the interest of the party as a show of appreciation of the good works of the Governor. Speaking during the occasion,the State APC chairman of APC, Mr Stanley Okoro Emagha, who also hails from Afikpo South LGA, lauded the massive crowd that came in support of Ekumankama, noting that it was a show of massive support for the APC in Edda. POLL He called on the people to always support Governor David Umahi and ensure that they participate fully in the general election to deliver the party beyond expectations.